lid date, an invalid week label, or an unknown entry id.\n### from rules\n- def Status: one of `draft`, `submitted`, `approved`, `rejected`.\n- def Day total: the sum of hours a person already has registered on one calendar date.\n- def RuleError: the typed error raised for an invalid value or an illegal status transition.\n### from ui-kit\n- def Token: a CSS custom property named `--ts-*` declared once inside the `:root` block of the stylesheet.\n- def Kit class: a CSS class named `ts-*` whose declarations reference tokens via `var(--ts-*)`, plain keywords, and plain size literals only.\n- def Page shell: a complete HTML5 document produced by `page(title, body)` that embeds the stylesheet inline.\n\n## Required modules (already generated)\n### timestore\n#### src/timestore/__init__.py\n```python\n\"\"\"Timesheet entry store backed by a JSON file.\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport json\n\nimport os\n\nimport re\n\nfrom datetime import date as _date\n\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nfrom typing import Any\n\nclass StoreError(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Raised for store misuse: missing path, invalid date/week, or unknown entry id.\"\"\"\n\nclass TimeStore:\n\n    def __init__(self, path: str | os.PathLike[str] | None=None) -> None:\n        ...\n\n    def add_entry(self, project: str, date: str, hours: float) -> dict[str, Any]:\n        ...\n\n    def get_entry(self, entry_id: int) -> dict[str, Any]:\n        ...\n\n    def update_entry(self, entry_id: int, **fields: Any) -> dict[str, Any]:\n        ...\n\n    def delete_entry(self, entry_id: int) -> None:\n        ...\n\n    def list_entries(self) -> list[dict[str, Any]]:\n        ...\n\n    def entries_for_project(self, project: str) -> list[dict[str, Any]]:\n        ...\n\n    def entries_for_date(self, date: str) -> list[dict[str, Any]]:\n        ...\n\n    def entries_for_week(self, week: str) -> list[dict[str, Any]]:\n        ...\n\n```\n### rules\n#### src/rules/__init__.py\n```python\n\"\"\"Pure business rules for timesheet entries.\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nMAX_DAY_HOURS = 24.0\n\nVALID_STATUSES = {'draft', 'submitted', 'approved', 'rejected'}\n\nLEGAL_TRANSITIONS = {('draft', 'submitted'): 'submitted', ('submitted', 'approved'): 'approved', ('submitted', 'rejected'): 'rejected'}\n\nclass RuleError(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Raised when a value is invalid or a status transition is illegal.\"\"\"\n\ndef validate_hours(hours: float, day_total: float=0.0) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Validate that ``hours`` is a positive addition that keeps the day within 24 hours.\"\"\"\n    ...\n\ndef transition(current: str, target: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Return ``target`` if moving from ``current`` to ``target`` is a legal status change.\"\"\"\n    ...\n\ndef assert_editable(status: str) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Raise ``RuleError`` if entries in ``status`` can no longer be edited.\"\"\"\n    ...\n\n```\n### ui-kit\n#### src/ui_kit/__init__.py\n```python\nfrom .page import page\n\nfrom .tokens import tokens_css\n\n__all__ = ['tokens_css', 'page']\n\n```\n#### src/ui_kit/page.py\n```python\nimport html\n\nfrom .tokens import tokens_css\n\ndef page(title, body):\n    \"\"\"Return a full HTML5 document embedding the ui-kit stylesheet and body.\"\"\"\n    ...\n\n```\n#### src/ui_kit/tokens.py\n```python\ndef tokens_css():\n    \"\"\"Return the ui-kit design-token stylesheet: one :root token block plus the ts- kit classes.\"\"\"\n    ...\n\n```\n\n## Current module files (already rendered for earlier units)\nExtend and stay consistent with this code; reuse its exact public names.\n#### src/timesheet_web/__init__.py\n```python\n\"\"\"Timesheet web application.\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport html\nfrom datetime import date as _date\n\nfrom fastapi import FastAPI, Form\nfrom fastapi.responses import HTMLResponse, RedirectResponse\n\nfrom rules import RuleError, validate_hours\nfrom timestore import StoreError, TimeStore\nfrom ui_kit import page\n\n__all__ 